# Global Design Rules

Apply these rules to all frontend UI work.

## Typography
- Headlines (`h1`, `h2`) must use `font-display` (Playfair Display).
- All other text must use `font-body` (Lato).
- Never use Inter, Roboto, or `system-ui` as display fonts.

## Colors
- Primary action: `bg-terracotta` (`#C8531A`) for buttons, CTAs, accents.
- Secondary: `bg-forest` (`#2D5016`) for certifications and success states.
- Accent: `text-gold` / `bg-gold` (`#F5C842`) for stats, star ratings, highlights.
- Page background: `bg-linen` (`#FAF7F2`) for light sections.
- Dark sections: `bg-espresso` (`#1A1208`) for video section, contact, footer.
- Body text: `text-warmBrown` (`#2C1A0E`).

## Animations
- Use Framer Motion `whileInView` for all scroll-triggered animations.
- Use `viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-100px" }}` for scroll-triggered animations.
- Do not animate on initial page load except Hero.
- Stagger delay between sibling elements: `0.15s`.
- Duration: `0.6-0.8s`, easing: `"easeOut"`.

## Spacing
- Section vertical padding: `py-24` on desktop and `py-16` on mobile.
- Max content width: `max-w-6xl mx-auto`.
- Section horizontal spacing: `px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`.

## Responsiveness
- Use a mobile-first approach.
- Use breakpoints: `sm` (640), `md` (768), `lg` (1024), `xl` (1280).
- Validate each section at `375px`.

## Accessibility
- Every image must have descriptive `alt` text.
- All interactive elements must have `focus-visible` styles.
- Form labels must be properly associated with inputs (`htmlFor` + `id`).
- Maintain minimum `4.5:1` color contrast ratio for all text.
